            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Here we have a <code>_get_age</code> <code>non-public method</code> and a <code>show_age</code> <code>public method</code>. The <code>show_age</code> can be used by our object (out of our class) and the <code>_get_age</code> only used inside our class definition (inside <code>show_age</code> method). But again: as a matter of convention.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
